Seven county commissioners were affected, among them Kwale’s Karuku Ngumo who was moved to Meru and Kisii’s Abdirizak Jaldesa who was posted to Samburu.
Meru’s commissioner Alan Njagi Macharia was transferred to Kisii.
John Kipng’etich Korir from Samburu was moved to Busia to fill in the vacancy left by Commissioner Joseph Murithi Kanyiri who was transferred to Kwale.





Moses Kipkoech Lilan, Homa Bay’s county commissioner, switched positions with Garissa’s Michael Mwangi Meru. 
The list copied to all regional commissioners showed that the transfers are with immediate effect.
They come barely four months after Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang’i announced the transfers of 15 county commissioners and 98 deputy county commissioners.
